article.description: — Collin Welp had 18 points as UC Irvine easily defeated Cal Poly 67-44 on Saturday.
article.headline: Welp scores 18 to lift UC Irvine over Cal Poly 67-44
article.linkText: Welp scores 18 to lift UC Irvine over Cal Poly 67-44
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. -- — Collin Welp had 18 points as UC Irvine easily defeated Cal Poly 67-44 on Saturday. JC Butler had 15 points for UC Irvine (8-4, 4-0 Big West Conference), which won its sixth straight game. Brad Greene added 12 points. Austin Johnson had seven rebounds. The Mustangs’ 27.9 field-goal percentage represented the worst mark by an UC Irvine opponent this season. Alimamy Koroma had 10 points and seven rebounds for the Mustangs (2-10, 0-6), who have now lost eight games in a row. The Anteaters improve to 2-0 against the Mustangs on the season. UC Irvine defeated Cal Poly 68-49 on Friday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
